<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - OIL PAN
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OIL PAN</title>
        <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prepare oil pan for installation by using a wire wheel to clean RTV from the oil pan lip.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BE SURE TO CLEAN ALL RTV FROM OIL PAN LIP CRANKCASE RAILS, FRONT COVER AND REAR OIL SEAL
                        CARRIER.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a 6 mm (1/4 in.) bead of RTV to the locations shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figures
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600788">7.88</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600789">7.89</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                :
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Where the crankcase and rear half of the front cover and the crankcase and rear oil seal
                    carrier contact each other.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Also apply a circle of RTV around the cupped plug crankcase orientation holes located on
                    the oil pan rails of the crankcase.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>
                            <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                            apply RTV more than 5 minutes before installing the oil pan.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1600787" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg6894" filename="../figeg6/EG6894.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.87 Installing Oil Pick-up Tube Support Bracket</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600788" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3577" filename="../figeg3/EG3577.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.88 Applying RTV To Crankcase</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600789" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5293" filename="../figeg5/EG5293.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.89 Applying RTV To Crankcase Rails</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the oil pan gasket onto the oil pan so that the seal bead of the gasket is
                <emph type="bold">TOWARD</emph>
                the crankcase and the edge marked
                <emph type="bold">FRONT</emph>
                is facing the front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil pan onto the crankcase. Place two (2) oil pan mounting bars on the pan oil
                rail and secure with the fourteen (14) long mounting bolts (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_207.xml" xrefid="ef1600790">7.90</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). Use the eight (8) shorter bolts to secure the oil pan to the front cover and rear oil seal carrier.
                Tighten bolts to the special torque value (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_207.xml" xrefid="ef1600791">7.91</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
